FBIS4-61162 "drsov086_u_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 Latvia Special Commission Formed To Monitor Treaty Implementation Special Commission Formed To Monitor Treaty Implementation LD0305215794 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 2000 GMT 3 May 94 LD0305215794 Riga Radio Riga Network Latvian BFN [Excerpt] [Announcer] Today at the session of the Cabinet of Ministers, a special government commission was formed whose task will be to monitor the implementation of the Latvian-Russian bilateral treaty. More about this from Minister of Justice Egils Levits: [Begin Levits recording] Now, when these agreements are concluded, we have to turn to the issues of the withdrawal of the Russian Army, and issues connected with taking over the Skrunda radar station. So firstly, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs has worked out a package of tasks to realize these agreements. Another question the government discussed today and adopted a resolution, on the rehabilitation of the Skrunda environment and the establishment of the repatriation fund for Russian military pensioners. [sentence as heard] This fund is being set up by the government with the intention of restoring the environment at Skrunda and the damage incurred by it, and to promote the repatriation of Russian military personnel and other military personnel. Certain contributions have already been promised from Sweden, from America, also other Scandinavian countries, who have agreed to invest funds to repatriate Russian military personnel from Latvia and in this way solve this problem. [passage omitted] [end recording]
